WEBVTT

00:04.505 --> 00:06.440
Roger?
Did you get glasses?

00:06.540 --> 00:08.242
Not glasses,
Francine.

00:08.342 --> 00:09.777
Transitions.

00:09.877 --> 00:11.379
(guitar riff plays)

00:11.479 --> 00:13.013
Best product
I've ever owned.

00:13.114 --> 00:14.748
Now I don't have to switch out
my regular glasses

00:14.848 --> 00:16.950
for sunglasses
every time I go outside.

00:17.051 --> 00:19.420
But you didn't wear
glasses before.

00:19.520 --> 00:22.256
But now I don't have
to switch 'em out!

00:22.356 --> 00:24.592
Ugh! Eyes hurt like
a bitch, though.

00:24.692 --> 00:27.261
That dead hobo must've
been blind as a bat.

00:27.361 --> 00:28.296
(clears throat)

00:28.396 --> 00:30.431
Mama? Papa?

00:30.531 --> 00:32.533
Barry invited me
to go with his family

00:32.633 --> 00:34.235
on a trip next month
to see the world's

00:34.335 --> 00:36.070
largest
chest of drawers.

00:36.170 --> 00:37.771
And I'd very much
like to go.

00:37.871 --> 00:39.073
I don't know.

00:39.173 --> 00:41.109
We've never
met Barry's parents.

00:41.209 --> 00:44.112
But judging from Barry, I think
it's safe to assume they're --

00:44.212 --> 00:46.647
and this is nothing against
Barry, we love Barry --

00:46.747 --> 00:49.117
monstrously stupid
sewer-people.

00:49.217 --> 00:51.051
Agreed.
Answer is a hard no.

00:51.152 --> 00:54.555
Another brilliant decision
by my genius parents.

00:54.655 --> 00:56.090
Sass-back.

00:56.190 --> 00:58.426
In my very own home.
That's it!

00:58.526 --> 01:00.994
Not only are you not
going on that trip, Smartmouth,

01:01.095 --> 01:02.430
you're grounded
for two weeks!

01:02.530 --> 01:04.064
You're so unfair!

01:04.165 --> 01:05.599
You never let me
do anything!

01:05.699 --> 01:06.767
I'm so frustrated,
I...

01:06.867 --> 01:07.935
(thud)

01:08.035 --> 01:10.604
Ooh, I feel it
coming on!

01:10.704 --> 01:12.473
Don't you do it,
young man.

01:12.573 --> 01:14.608
I think I'm gonna
go bananas!

01:14.708 --> 01:16.610
-Do not go bananas...
-It's gonna happen!

01:16.710 --> 01:18.779
-You best not go bananas, boy!
-I'm gonna go bananas!

01:18.879 --> 01:20.281
Do it, Steve.
Go bananas.

01:20.381 --> 01:21.915
-(scrapes)
-(groans)

01:22.015 --> 01:24.352
Aaahgg-blahh-jyaah!

01:24.452 --> 01:26.820
(screaming indistinctly)

01:26.920 --> 01:27.955
Is this what you want?!

01:28.055 --> 01:29.790
Are you happy now?!

01:29.890 --> 01:33.494
(screaming)

01:37.665 --> 01:39.700
(continues screaming)

01:42.470 --> 01:45.806
Is this what you wanted?!
Me goin' bananas!

01:45.906 --> 01:47.708
(continues screaming)

01:47.808 --> 01:50.844
Sounds like Steve's
goin' bananas again.

01:50.944 --> 01:51.945
(continues screaming)

01:52.045 --> 01:53.013
(thud)

01:53.113 --> 01:54.114
Yep.

01:54.215 --> 01:56.617
(patriotic music plays)

01:56.717 --> 01:59.287
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

01:59.387 --> 02:03.224
♪ I got a feelin' that
it's gonna be a wonderful day ♪

02:03.324 --> 02:06.560
♪ The sun in the sky
has a smile on his face ♪

02:06.660 --> 02:10.631
♪ And he's shinin' a salute
to the American race ♪

02:12.500 --> 02:15.803
♪ Oh, boy, it's swell to say ♪

02:15.903 --> 02:18.071
-♪ Good -- ♪
-♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:18.172 --> 02:19.373
Aah!

02:20.708 --> 02:24.044
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:24.144 --> 02:26.547
♪♪

02:26.647 --> 02:29.250
(sighs) I wish my parents
were more like yours, Barry.

02:29.350 --> 02:30.718
They let you
do whatever you want.

02:30.818 --> 02:33.487
I once spent the night
at Claim Jumper's!

02:33.587 --> 02:34.488
That's it!

02:34.588 --> 02:36.023
Claim Jumpers?

02:36.123 --> 02:37.325
Okay, but I think
they'll be

02:37.425 --> 02:38.826
on the look-out
for me this time.

02:38.926 --> 02:41.662
No, if our parents
became friends,

02:41.762 --> 02:44.698
yours are so chill,
maybe they'd rub off on mine.

02:44.798 --> 02:46.500
Then we'd be able to
hang out all the time

02:46.600 --> 02:47.701
and do whatever we want!

02:47.801 --> 02:49.570
It'll be like The Purge!

02:49.670 --> 02:51.439
We could
go on a rampage!

02:51.539 --> 02:54.875
-Rampage! Rampage! Rampage!
-Rampage! Rampage! Rampage!

02:57.445 --> 03:00.448
Everybody, the eclipse
is about to start!

03:00.548 --> 03:03.050
Everybody, take a pair
of special glasses

03:03.150 --> 03:04.852
from my giant tub of glasses.

03:04.952 --> 03:07.721
(chuckles)
I think these bad boys

03:07.821 --> 03:10.057
will do me just fine,
thank you very much.

03:10.157 --> 03:11.792
Roger, you could really
damage your eyes

03:11.892 --> 03:14.094
looking at the eclipse
with just your glasses.

03:14.194 --> 03:16.730
Uh, they're not just glasses,
Klaus, they're...

03:16.830 --> 03:18.366
-Transitions.
-...a lifestyle.

03:18.466 --> 03:20.268
(guitar riff plays)

03:20.368 --> 03:22.270
(gasps)
It's starting!

03:25.138 --> 03:27.908
Ooh.

03:28.008 --> 03:31.412
TUTTLE:
And here comes the sun!

03:32.446 --> 03:35.416
(sizzling)

03:35.516 --> 03:37.585
Pretty neat...
Pretty neat.

03:37.685 --> 03:39.753
Welp, I'm blind.

03:39.853 --> 03:41.322
I do not blame
the glasses, though.

03:41.422 --> 03:43.557
Good product.
Solid product.

03:47.995 --> 03:50.163
I can't believe Steve
talked us into going to dinner

03:50.264 --> 03:53.100
with that goon Barry
and his cave-troll parents.

03:53.200 --> 03:55.068
Hey, I don't wanna
do this, either.

03:55.168 --> 03:57.237
You think chowing down
on swamp stew

03:57.338 --> 04:00.674
with a couple of real-life ogres
is at the top of my bucket list?

04:00.774 --> 04:02.676
I think when you two
finally actually meet

04:02.776 --> 04:04.778
Barry's parents, you're
really gonna like them.

04:04.878 --> 04:05.779
Nope.

04:05.879 --> 04:08.349
(doorbell rings)

04:08.449 --> 04:11.285
Stan.
Francine.

04:11.385 --> 04:12.520
Outta sight.

04:14.788 --> 04:16.657
Well, get the heck
in here, you three.

04:16.757 --> 04:19.760
The fondue's
startin' to skin up.

04:19.860 --> 04:23.964
Whoa!
This place is incredible!

04:24.064 --> 04:26.800
So much mahogany.

04:26.900 --> 04:28.268
Thick wood.

04:28.369 --> 04:29.770
A man's wood.

04:29.870 --> 04:31.372
Mahalo. Mahalo.

04:31.472 --> 04:33.541
Stan-o, c'mere, I gotta
show you the hi-fi.

04:33.641 --> 04:34.842
Outta sight.

04:34.942 --> 04:37.778
Mom, you know
Mrs. Robinson here makes

04:37.878 --> 04:39.947
a mean
Harvey Wallbanger...

04:40.047 --> 04:41.782
Oh, it's just vodka with
some orange juice

04:41.882 --> 04:43.384
and a scooch of Galliano.

04:43.484 --> 04:46.320
You put things
in your vodka?

04:46.420 --> 04:50.558
Ooh, girl, I feel like I'm
at the Ritz Charleston!

04:50.658 --> 04:52.526
You know, Dad,
Mr. Robinson played

04:52.626 --> 04:53.961
a little ball back in college.

04:54.061 --> 04:55.162
Ted, you played
a little ball?

04:55.262 --> 04:56.364
Yep, little ball.

04:56.464 --> 04:57.631
Little college ball.

04:57.731 --> 04:59.667
I'll be damned,
a little ball...

04:59.767 --> 05:01.735
Little ball up
at San Jose State.

05:01.835 --> 05:03.136
A little ball.

05:03.236 --> 05:04.738
-Hey, Franny!
-It was just a little ball.

05:04.838 --> 05:06.239
You know Ted here
played a little ball?

05:06.340 --> 05:07.508
Ted played
a little ball?

05:07.608 --> 05:09.377
Little ball up
at San Jose State.

05:09.477 --> 05:11.879
I was actually coached
by John Elway's dad.

05:11.979 --> 05:13.080
(whistles)

05:13.180 --> 05:14.515
Have you ever met
John Elway?

05:14.615 --> 05:16.750
No. But I've always
wanted to.

05:16.850 --> 05:17.918
Me, too.

05:18.018 --> 05:19.052
Wow.

05:19.152 --> 05:20.888
♪ With the rain in Shambala ♪

05:20.988 --> 05:23.391
♪ Ah, ooh ♪

05:23.491 --> 05:26.927
C'mon, Franny,
gimme a bump, sister!

05:27.027 --> 05:30.063
-Ooh! Whoop!
-(laughs)

05:30.163 --> 05:33.867
♪ Ah, ooh, yeah ♪

05:33.967 --> 05:35.703
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

05:37.738 --> 05:40.173
Bli-i-i-i-nd.

05:40.273 --> 05:41.942
Sa-a-a-a-d.

05:42.042 --> 05:43.844
-(light switch clicks)
-Roger, we are not

05:43.944 --> 05:45.779
going to
let you just wallow in --

05:45.879 --> 05:47.347
Wait, why are you
in a wheelchair?

05:47.448 --> 05:49.282
I didn't know what kind of chair
I was sitting down in

05:49.383 --> 05:50.451
because I'm blind!

05:50.551 --> 05:52.953
(sobs)

05:53.053 --> 05:55.689
C'mon, Roger, you can still
live a full life.

05:55.789 --> 05:57.090
Can I, Steve?

05:57.190 --> 05:59.059
I'll never see another
Thomas Kinkade,

05:59.159 --> 06:01.395
or a fat guy
falling over on a Rascal.

06:01.495 --> 06:03.464
I guess I'll just have to
kill myself.

06:03.564 --> 06:05.232
Not on my watch!

06:05.332 --> 06:06.934
We're making it
our mission in life

06:07.034 --> 06:09.803
to help you rediscover
your trademark joie de vivre!

06:09.903 --> 06:12.239
We'll see, Francine.

06:12.339 --> 06:13.707
We'll see.

06:13.807 --> 06:15.709
♪ Just an old fashioned
love song ♪

06:15.809 --> 06:18.311
Seriously, how do two
smokin' hot 10s

06:18.412 --> 06:19.747
like you
give birth to this --

06:19.847 --> 06:21.148
and this is nothing
against Barry here,

06:21.248 --> 06:23.651
I adore Barry, I mean this
in the kindest way possible --

06:23.751 --> 06:25.318
stomach-turning
hobgoblin?

06:25.419 --> 06:27.755
(laughter)

06:27.855 --> 06:29.790
Ah!
You got my number.

06:29.890 --> 06:31.124
Oh, we just like
to think of him

06:31.224 --> 06:33.393
as our groovy,
little butterball.

06:33.494 --> 06:35.729
Barry, where've you been
hiding these two?

06:35.829 --> 06:37.097
They should hide him!

06:37.197 --> 06:39.332
-(laughter)
-Whoa!

06:39.433 --> 06:42.135
Cease fire!
Cease fire!

06:42.235 --> 06:43.571
Mom, Dad, may I go
to the bathroom --

06:43.671 --> 06:44.805
Do whatever you want,
we don't care.

06:47.107 --> 06:49.977
(whistling)

06:52.446 --> 06:54.482
-(light switch clicks)
-Whup, wrong room.

06:54.582 --> 06:56.984
Never been in this one before...

06:58.619 --> 07:01.288
(water sloshes)

07:01.388 --> 07:03.924
(Disco music playing
on speakers)

07:04.024 --> 07:05.826
♪♪

07:05.926 --> 07:08.962
So You Want
To Be A Swinger?

07:09.062 --> 07:12.533
So You're Currently
A Swinger?

07:12.633 --> 07:16.103
So You Want To Swing with
Your Son's Friend's Parents?!

07:17.204 --> 07:18.806
(gasps)

07:18.906 --> 07:22.275
Barry's parents aren't gonna
rub off on Mom and Dad.

07:22.375 --> 07:24.778
They're gonna rub one out
on Mom and Dad!

07:24.878 --> 07:27.147
That was probably more
disgusting than it needed to be,

07:27.247 --> 07:28.816
but, oh, my God!

07:33.487 --> 07:35.288
Did you know
your parents are swingers?

07:35.388 --> 07:37.625
Oh, yeah! They're always
saying stuff like,

07:37.725 --> 07:39.359
"You're money
and you don't even know it,"

07:39.459 --> 07:42.295
or "You're so money."
Or "That's money baby."

07:42.395 --> 07:44.632
Listen, my parents
are prudes.

07:44.732 --> 07:46.534
If I don't get them out
of here before yours

07:46.634 --> 07:49.169
come onto them, they might
never let us hang out again.

07:49.269 --> 07:51.071
-Understand?
-No!

07:51.171 --> 07:52.873
-Treehouse time!
-Treehouse time!

07:52.973 --> 07:54.642
Treehouse time?

07:54.742 --> 07:57.210
Have fun, you two!

07:57.310 --> 07:59.246
I spend most nights
in the treehouse

07:59.346 --> 08:01.849
while my mom and dad
have wrestling parties.

08:01.949 --> 08:05.085
Time to put on our blindfolds
and headphones!

08:05.185 --> 08:08.421
(muffled music plays)

08:10.924 --> 08:13.226
CONNIE: Yoo-hoo! Stan!
Francine!

08:13.326 --> 08:15.696
Bananas Foster
in the hot tub!

08:15.796 --> 08:17.064
Bananas Foster?

08:17.164 --> 08:18.566
With the bananas shaped
like penises

08:18.666 --> 08:20.267
and the ice cream
shaped like boobs?

08:20.367 --> 08:21.535
I gotta stop them!

08:21.635 --> 08:23.571
(grunts)

08:23.671 --> 08:25.172
(grunts, screams, thuds)

08:26.674 --> 08:29.376
-Stan! Nice suit.
-It's yours.

08:29.476 --> 08:31.712
Yeah, but you really
fill it out.

08:31.812 --> 08:33.714
Give it a nice shape.

08:33.814 --> 08:35.415
I need to go
to the hospital!

08:35.515 --> 08:36.850
(dramatic chord strikes)

08:36.950 --> 08:38.518
Ugh, it's always
the hospital

08:38.619 --> 08:39.553
with you, Steve!

08:39.653 --> 08:42.022
First when you were born
and now again?

08:42.122 --> 08:44.091
ROGER: This is stupid.
I can't see.

08:44.191 --> 08:45.258
Why are we going to a movie?

08:45.358 --> 08:46.927
Because you're going to
experience life

08:47.027 --> 08:48.228
just as you did before.

08:48.328 --> 08:49.763
Okay, but I've literally

08:49.863 --> 08:52.065
never gone
to a movie before.

08:52.165 --> 08:54.568
GOONIE: Sloth?! You mean
the monster that killed Chunk's

08:54.668 --> 08:56.904
entire family after
he went to live with them?

08:57.004 --> 08:58.739
-Now, who said that?
-The other kid.

08:58.839 --> 08:59.773
-Shh!
-Shh!

08:59.873 --> 09:02.109
GOONIE #2:
Goonies never look back!

09:02.209 --> 09:03.443
Was that the catchphrase?

09:03.543 --> 09:04.778
-What'd he say?
-What?

09:04.878 --> 09:06.880
-You're blind, not deaf.
-Huh?

09:06.980 --> 09:08.716
Sorry, I'm listening
to a podcast.

09:08.816 --> 09:10.417
-(cellphone chimes)
-Oh, can you read this for me?

09:10.517 --> 09:12.886
I'm expecting a text
from my friend McDaniel.

09:12.986 --> 09:15.255
-Shh!
-Which character was that?

09:15.355 --> 09:17.224
-That wasn't from the --
-Is it from McDaniel?

09:17.324 --> 09:18.726
I'm fighting with McDaniel
right now.

09:18.826 --> 09:20.994
So, if it's from McDaniel,
do not write back.

09:21.094 --> 09:23.563
-It's from Rafi.
-Uch, I'm fighting with Rafi.

09:23.664 --> 09:25.065
He sucks so hard.

09:25.165 --> 09:26.433
Here, I'm gonna dictate
a message to you...

09:26.533 --> 09:28.235
-Shut the hell up!
-Shut up, you dick!

09:28.335 --> 09:29.803
Get outta here,
why don'tcha?!

09:29.903 --> 09:32.906
Fine! I told you this was
a stupid idea!

09:33.006 --> 09:34.608
-Oh!
-Ah!

09:34.708 --> 09:37.077
That's it! I don't care
if you're blind, bro!

09:37.177 --> 09:38.679
I'mma kick your ass!

09:38.779 --> 09:40.147
Aah! No, no, no, no!

09:40.247 --> 09:42.582
(crowd gasping)

09:42.683 --> 09:45.285
Did I just...
beat that guy up?

09:45.385 --> 09:46.519
Of course!

09:46.620 --> 09:49.690
Losing my eyesight must have
sharpened my other senses!

09:49.790 --> 09:50.924
-Actually --
-Shh.

09:51.024 --> 09:52.459
Look how happy he is!

09:52.559 --> 09:54.527
Especially my sense
of smell.

09:54.628 --> 09:55.663
(sniffs)

09:55.763 --> 09:57.865
You, sir,
are a pedophile.

09:59.767 --> 10:02.169
♪♪

10:02.269 --> 10:04.371
(mumbling)
...swingers...

10:04.471 --> 10:05.372
'Sup?

10:05.472 --> 10:07.340
I -- What are you doing
in my room?

10:07.440 --> 10:09.042
Just going through
your stuff.

10:09.142 --> 10:12.145
Jeez, you look stressed.
What's going on?

10:12.245 --> 10:13.947
Mom and Dad loved
Barry's parents,

10:14.047 --> 10:15.849
but it turns out
they're swingers.

10:15.949 --> 10:17.885
And now I'm afraid if
Mom and Dad find out,

10:17.985 --> 10:19.887
they won't let me be
friends with Barry anymore.

10:19.987 --> 10:21.354
Don't worry
about that.

10:21.454 --> 10:23.290
Worry about Mom and Dad
becoming swingers.

10:23.390 --> 10:25.525
What?!
They would never do that.

10:25.625 --> 10:26.559
Oh, yeah?

10:26.694 --> 10:28.696
Sounds like Barry's parents
are grooming them.

10:28.796 --> 10:30.063
It's only a matter
of time before

10:30.163 --> 10:31.531
they claim their prey.
(chuckles)

10:31.631 --> 10:32.833
Mom and Dad won't know
what hit 'em.

10:32.933 --> 10:34.067
And then what?

10:34.167 --> 10:35.502
Divorce. 100%.

10:35.602 --> 10:36.536
They won't be able to
handle it.

10:36.636 --> 10:37.671
Mom, sure.

10:37.771 --> 10:39.306
She's the female
Wilt Chamberlain.

10:39.406 --> 10:41.008
But, Dad?
Not a chance.

10:41.108 --> 10:43.877
No way it doesn't destroy
their marriage.

10:43.977 --> 10:46.479
Oh, hell,
yeah, nunchucks!

10:46.579 --> 10:48.882
Michelangelo!
Michelangelo!

10:48.982 --> 10:51.518
See ya later, nerd.

10:51.618 --> 10:53.053
(laughter)

10:53.153 --> 10:55.488
Ugh, sorry about
dragging you

10:55.588 --> 10:57.224
to that awful
dinner last night.

10:57.324 --> 10:59.860
How 'bout that Connie and Ted?
What a couple of shitheads,

10:59.960 --> 11:01.228
-am I right?
-FRANCINE: What?

11:01.328 --> 11:03.697
Connie and Ted
are outta sight, man!

11:03.797 --> 11:06.366
Yeah. They actually suggested
hanging out again sometime.

11:06.466 --> 11:08.335
Absolutely not!

11:08.435 --> 11:09.770
Now, you listen to me,

11:09.870 --> 11:12.372
I forbid you from hanging out
with Barry's parents.

11:12.472 --> 11:14.875
Uh, I don't know
what's gotten into you,

11:14.975 --> 11:17.177
but how exactly
are you gonna stop us?

11:17.277 --> 11:19.012
"Uh," how about
this?

11:19.112 --> 11:21.114
If you so much as talk
to them again,

11:21.214 --> 11:23.550
I'll take away
your Internet privileges.

11:23.650 --> 11:25.018
I pay for
the Internet.

11:25.118 --> 11:27.755
Yeah, but only I know
how to set it up.

11:27.855 --> 11:30.223
He's got us by
the long-hairs, Francine.

11:30.323 --> 11:33.060
Ted suggested we grow out our
pubic hair. It's natural.

11:33.160 --> 11:35.528
I can change the Wi-Fi
password in two minutes,

11:35.628 --> 11:37.965
and it's goodbye,
Jake Paul, Dad!

11:38.065 --> 11:39.366
-(gasps)
-You dick!

11:39.466 --> 11:40.768
What's your problem?!

11:40.868 --> 11:42.402
You're the ones
with the problem

11:42.502 --> 11:44.637
because you two
are grounded!

11:44.738 --> 11:47.207
-You're so unfair!
-Go to your room!

11:47.307 --> 11:49.042
-We hate you!
-We hate you!

11:49.142 --> 11:52.045
(footsteps ascending stairs)

11:52.145 --> 11:53.546
(door slams)

11:53.646 --> 11:54.815
(music plays in distance)

11:54.915 --> 11:57.885
♪ Jeremiah was a bullfrog ♪

11:57.985 --> 12:00.720
♪ Was a good friend of mine ♪

12:00.821 --> 12:02.589
Roger was so happy
when he thought

